result.execSummary:
The defendant Terry L. Eilenfeldt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 8:52 am [Clerk SH]
Defendant Terry L. Eilenfeldt in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing Arguments by Counsel

On Count #1, the Court sentences Mr. Eilenfeldt to 6 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 3 years and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 3 years. This sentence is IMPOSED AND STAYED and the Court places the Defendant on Probation for 3 years with conditions:
--serve 90 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-release privileges for employment, AODA & counseling; to commence on or before 11/27/15 by 6:00 pm 
--Defendant is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--AODA Assessment (within 30 days) & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--No acts/threats of violence
--To undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--Maintain absolute sobriety
--No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores
--No possession or consumption of alcohol
--To pay statutory court costs and DNA surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--To pay $359 subpoena fees

Days credit for time already served: 1 days
Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form given to the Defendant

If revoked: 
The Court finds that the Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 
Conditions of Probation become conditions of extended supervision

Case called at 1:17 pm.  

Defendant Terry L. Eilenfeldt in custody, via video from the Jefferson County Jail with Attorney Yelena Zarwell from the Jefferson County Public Defenders Office. Public Service Special Prosecutor Attorney Melanie Flint appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Attorney Zarwell informs the Court that the video connection is sight and sound sufficient.
Attorney Zarwell informs the Court that the defendant qualifies for SPD representation.

Court reviews Conflict Review Worksheet. The Court discloses, under SCR 60.04 that in the Court's former capacity as Jefferson County District Attorney, attorneys that DA Wambach supervised did prosecute Mr. Eilenfeldt. The Court does not feel that any disqualification or recusal is needed. Court finds no conflict and signs the Conflict Review Worksheet.

Service of Complaint admitted; reading waived; maximum penalties recited.
Court verifies with the Defendant that the DOB and address listed on the Criminal Complaint are correct. 
Court has reviewed the Criminal Complaint and finds that it states Probable Cause to support Count #1.

Court requires $5,000 signature bond, with conditions: 
-No possession or ingestion of alcohol 
-No presence in bars, taverns or liquor stores 
-No acts or threats of violence  
-No contact with DJD (DOB 01/14/06), Becky Jenne, and Daniel Hamilton 
-No presence at 709 Dodge Street, Watertown
-Defendant may return to 709 Dodge Street on one occasion, with law enforcement, to collect personal belongings. 

Preliminary Hearing time limits waived by both parties. 

Recess: 1:29 pm
